This lab demonstrates how an attacker can gain unauthorized access to a system running Telnet, steal clearâ€‘text credentials over the network, and escalate to full system control.

Telnet is an outdated protocol that transmits all data â€” including usernames and passwords â€” in plaintext, making it highly vulnerable.

ğŸ” 1. Service Discovery

Initial port scan:

